 6) Peritonitis (inflammation of the peritoneum) caused by Candida
**A note on fungal infection prophylaxis**
Patients receiving bone marrow transplantation who are treated with cytotoxic chemotherapy and/or radiation therapy may be predisposed to candida infections, and may receive fluconazole as prophylactic therapy.[L11043]
**A note on laboratory testing**
Obtaining specimens for fungal culture and other important laboratory studies such as serology or pathology is advised before starting fluconazole therapy in order to isolate the organisms to be eliminated through treatment. It is permissible to start therapy before the results are available, however, adjusting the therapy once laboratory results confirm the causative organism may be necessary.[L11043]', '', '', 1403, '2023-05-04', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
